        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>On some vehicles operating at high altitudes, the charge air cooler temperature tends to cause the
                    viscous fan drives to engage late or at higher coolant temperatures. The vehicles susceptible are
                    equipped with International T 444E engines, SA-75 viscous fan clutches and MD-9 Nylon fans. When
                    this occurs, the fan drive engages at higher than normal coolant temperatures resulting in
                    overheating of the engine. The addition of a air inlet baffle over the charge air cooler will result
                    in earlier fan engagement which allows the fan to maintain lower coolant temperatures.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
