        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <stitle>TSI 02-12-18 - Viscous Fan Drive "Temperature Engagement" Variability</stitle>
            <title>Service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To prevent property damage or personal injury allow the engine cooling system to cool
                        sufficiently before proceeding with this service procedure.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">If the vehicle is equipped with A/C, the condenser will have to be unbolted from the
                    radiator housing and moved out of the way.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the radiator for debris and clean if necessary. Refer to TSI-02-12-01 for the
                    proper cleaning procedure.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the lower two bolts holding the charge air cooler to the center support bar shown
                    in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0212181">Figure 1</hotlnk>.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the air inlet baffle positioned on the bumper side of the charge air cooler as
                    shown in
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0212181">Figure 1</hotlnk>. Use the two bolts that were removed in Step 3. above.
                    Make certain the air inlet baffle covers the Charge Air Cooler and not the radiator.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Re-install the A/C condenser if removed in Step 1. above.</para>
            </step1>
